Subsection 1(2) of the Regulations also includes general information specific to references to the CFR. It should be noted that when the Regulations refers to the CFR, they exclude:
* references to the EPA or its Administrator using any kind of discretion;
* references to the Secretary of Transportation exercising discretion in any way;
* alternative standards related to fleet averages, other averages, emission credits, small volume
* meaning that if, for instance, a company participates in
* standards established by any authority other than the EPA or evidence of conformity with any

As per subsections 5(1) and (2) of the Regulations, the prescribed classes of vehicles and engines set out in the Regulations are as follows:
* Class 2B and Class 3 heavy-duty vehicles;
* vocational vehicles;
* tractors;
* heavy-duty incomplete vehicles; and
* heavy-duty engines.
